* image *image_open(char *fname);

  Open file FNAME.

  Returns pointer to image on succes, NULL on error.



METHODS:

* int image_close(image *im);

  Close and free image.

  Returns 0 on success, -1 on error.


* char *image_get_palette(image *im);

  Get palette of image as a row of samples.

  Returns pointer to palette on success, NULL on error.


* int image_read(image *im, char **bp);

  Read one row of image data and point BP at it.

  Returns 0 on success, -1 on error.


* int image_read_finish(image *im, int abortp);

  Finish reading image data.  If ABORTP, image might not have been
  read compiletely.

  Returns 0 on success, -1 on error.


* int image_read_start(image *im);

  Start reading image data.  Must be called before calls to image_read().

  Returns 0 on success, -1 on error.


* int image_set_cspace(image *im, image_cspace cspace);

  Request image data in color space CSPACE.

  Returns 0 if transformation supported, -1 otherwise.


* int image_set_depth(image *im, int depth);

  Request image data with DEPTH bits per component.

  Returns 0 if transformation supported, -1 otherwise.


* int image_set_size(image *im, int width, int height);

  Request that image be scaled to WIDTHxHEIGHT.

  Returns 0 if transformation supported, -1 otherwise.
